LABORATORY VALUES
Hemoglobin is currently 9.8 and most recent creatinine was 1.8.
IMPRESSION/PLAN
#1 Colon mass
#2 Iron-deficiency anemia
PLAN
Mr. Smith is an 86-year-old male who has multiple medical problems in the face of an hepatic flexure mass and iron-deficiency anemia, which has required blood transfusions in just two-weeks' time.  The patient is not obstructed from this mass.  We will await the pathology results in order to discuss further options for this patient.  I did review with the patient that since his mass is bleeding and it has bled in only two-weeks' time since his last transfusion that he may benefit from having a resection. This is the likely etiology for his anemia, given that his extensive workup previously has been otherwise unremarkable.  The patient, in general, wishes to be aggressive; however, we must make sure that he is able to tolerate a surgery and has adequate preoperative cardiac clearance.  We will ultimately await the pathology biopsy results in order to better delineate our plan of care.  If there is carcinoma in the biopsy, he should have a staging CT-scan of the abdomen and pelvis and a recent chest X-ray.
This patient will be discussed with Dr. Hutchinson.  Thank-you for this consult.

